Name: Bahla Fort
Description: Bahla Fort - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Massive mud-brick fort from the 13th century.

Name: Bat
Description: Archaeological Sites of Bat, Al-Khutm and Al-Ayn - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Bronze Age necropolises and settlements.

Name: Land of Frankincense
Description: Land of Frankincense - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient frankincense trade sites including Shisr and Khor Rori.

Name: Aflaj Irrigation Systems
Description: Aflaj Irrigation Systems of Oman - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient water management systems still in use today.
